automated multitask deep learning system:
It utilized a Visual Geometry Group Network 16 (VGG16) for preliminary image screening.
It incorporated a rotator cuff multitask learning (RC-MTL) model for detailed classification of SST injuries.
The RC-MTL model has a shared underlying structure (ResNet-101 with a convolutional block attention module (CBAM)) and four independent task classifiers
A multistage decision model was used to logically reorganize and aggregate the results from the RC-MTL model
